Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.78,0:30:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\an8\blur3}观众提问
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.96,0:33:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\blur3}奥尔特云是一个假设的包围者太阳系的球体云团\N布满着不活跃的彗星
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.75,0:37:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\an8\blur3}卡西尼号是土星探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.84,0:37:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\an8\blur3}新视野号是木星探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上溯至宇宙初始 周遭还只是一片漆黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知何时 忽地一声巨响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then... Bang!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间空间以及物质皆由此发端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Giving birth to an endless expanding existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此后不断膨胀 延伸 永无止境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一天 新的发现都在不断为我们解开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蕴藏于这里的那些神秘莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the mysterious, the mind-blowing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人大开眼界 致命的秘密{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the deadly secrets of a place we call{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称这个地方为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.96,0:00:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}纵贯它45亿年的历史{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Throughout its 4.5 billion-year history,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.71,0:00:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们的太阳系目睹了一场大规模屠杀{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}our Solar System has witnessed carnage on a colossal scale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.50,0:00:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}时不时地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Time and again,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.62,0:00:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大灾难就会粉碎行星的平静{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}catastrophes have shattered the planetary peace.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.60,0:00:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在正确位置的巨大撞击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A large impact striking at the right location{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.45,0:00:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}能够使这整个星球完全消失{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}could have caused the whole planet to go off kilter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.45,0:00:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}世界将被撞毁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Worlds have collided{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或者变成遍布火山{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or been paved over by runaway volcanism...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.97,0:00:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}甚至会被撞出太阳系的范围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or even ejected from the Sun's grasp.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.58,0:00:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在太阳系这种恐怖活动的笼罩下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}No planet has provided sanctuary{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.07,0:00:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}没有行星能够提供避难所{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from the Solar System's reign of terror.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.46,0:01:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果小行星处于高速状态下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you have an asteroid slam in at high speed,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.60,0:01:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}小块的水银将会从表面飞离出来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}then little bits of Mercury will go flying off the surface,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.18,0:01:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一些水银块不可避免会撞向地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and inevitably, some of those chunks will hit Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.73,0:01:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果你认为地球是一个安全的避难所{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So, if you think Earth is a safe haven,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.86,0:01:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那么 再想想吧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}think again.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.04,0:01:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从最初的剧变 让行星成形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}From the oldest cataclysm that rocked the planets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}到最终的大灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to the ultimate disaster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让一切灰飞烟灭{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that will one day blow them to oblivion,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}系好安全带 我们即将倒数回顾{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}fasten your seatbelts, as we count down...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}改变行星的十大灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The ten greatest catastrophes that changed the planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球 这颗行星如今非常的平静{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Planet Earth... Peaceful today...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.28,0:01:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}过去也曾经历过大碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}has suffered its share of collisions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.93,0:01:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}火山大喷发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}massive eruptions,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.46,0:01:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以及物种大灭绝{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and mass extinctions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.11,0:01:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与太阳系其他兄弟姐妹行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But most Earthly disasters pale in comparison{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.24,0:01:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所发生的毁灭性灾难相比{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with the apocalyptic traumas{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.94,0:02:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球遭受的大部分灾难显得微不足道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that befell our siblings in the Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.48,0:02:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳系诞生于大漩涡之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Solar System was born in a maelstrom,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.45,0:02:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}数之不清的巨大石块相互撞击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as billions of rocky boulders collided{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}形成了我们今日所知的众多行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to form the planets we know today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.70,0:02:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}暴力造就了太阳系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The birth of the Solar System was full of violence.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}各种小行星体以及原行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There were all sorts of planetesimals and protoplanets{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.51,0:02:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}相互撞击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}colliding with one another{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或经过另外一个时 太接近{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or going close past one another{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.63,0:02:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而造成相互排斥{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and ejecting each other,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.75,0:02:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而把彼此推向太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or sending each other down toward the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以 只有一些行星幸存下来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so, you know, only a few planets survived.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.48,0:02:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳系之初 非常像{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The early Solar System was very much{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一场宇宙弹球比赛{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a cosmic pinball machine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这场比赛之中充斥着相互作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where you had lots of impacts{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以及相互撞击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and lots of collisions taking place,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.48,0:02:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}毁灭行星 形成行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}destroying planets, forming planets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.22,0:02:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}行星解体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}breaking apart planets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.24,0:02:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}创造出了我们今日所见到的一切{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}creating everything that we see today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.79,0:02:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但在很久以前 太阳系并不是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But long ago, it would not be the type of place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:02:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}适合我们生存的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that we'd want to live.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.42,0:03:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当幸存下来的行星成型{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As the surviving planets took shape,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.62,0:03:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这种暴力现象却更厉害了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the violence only intensified.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.97,0:03:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}首先 十大行星大灾难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}First, and earliest, on our countdown{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}排在第十位的是{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the ten worst planetary cataclysms...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.27,0:03:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星地幔危机{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Mercury Mantle Disaster{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星 是最接近太阳的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mercury, the closest planet to our Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.49,0:03:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也是太阳系中最小的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is also the runt of the Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.32,0:03:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家们认为这颗弱小的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now scientists think the puniest planet{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.58,0:03:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}却承受着宇宙最强大的冲击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was dealt one of nature's mightiest blows.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}对科学家来说 水星一直是个迷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mercury's a mystery to scientists.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.32,0:03:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星的内核是铁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The iron core inside Mercury{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.36,0:03:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大约占到了水星体积的40%{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is about 40% of the volume of the planet,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}比如说 在地球上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}whereas on Earth, for example,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地核仅占到其体积的20%{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the core is only about 20% of the Earth's total volume,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.40,0:03:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}哪怕地球比水星大了三倍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}even though Earth is about three times larger than Mercury.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.78,0:03:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在行星领域中 水星是一道难题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mercury is a bit of a conundrum in planetary science.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.25,0:03:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星就像是太阳系中的大钢球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's like the Solar System's big ball bearing sitting out there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:03:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎是纯粹的钢铁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's almost like a pure piece of steel.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.16,0:04:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这么小的行星 密度怎么会如此高{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}How did that little planet get so dense?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.14,0:04:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一个理论称{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One theory holds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.42,0:04:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}行星之间的碰撞就是罪魁祸首{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that a planetary collision was the culprit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.17,0:04:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但撞击为何能增加行星的密度呢{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But how could an impact make a planet dense?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.93,0:04:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}想象一下 撞上水星的是个大炮弹{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}By envisioning Mercury's cosmic attacker as a cannonball,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.56,0:04:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有助于我们理解当时发生了什么{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we can help re-imagine what happened.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们点燃美国革命中使用过的大炮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Let's fire cannonballs from this American revolution cannon{\r}
